%section#banner
  - unless Admin::Banner.first.nil?
    - chosenbanner = Admin::Banner.all.sample # KT@HOME - PerfTune: This is not ideal since _all_ banners get pulled into memory to use just one. It would be better to tell the database that we just want a random banner. But that's also tough to do in a database agnostic way. Additionally selection of a banner should be done in the controller or model rather than here.
    = link_to image_tag(chosenbanner.image(:medium), size: '468x60', alt: :banner, class: 'banner'), chosenbanner.url
